## GAME 4: BLITZ

**What changed:** New game, needs building. A 90-second speed round where the player names as many games as possible within a daily theme.

**Core mechanic:**
- Daily theme shown (e.g. "Mario Games", "90s Platformers")
- 90-second countdown timer (ring SVG, turns red at 15s)
- Player types game names. Each correct answer spawns a floating word node in the arena above the input
- Bronze (5), Silver (12), Gold (20) milestones

**Word cloud arena:**
- Correct answers: white pill nodes drift slowly, bounce off walls, connected by faint lines when close (canvas overlay)
- Wrong answers: red pill, shake animation, fade out
- Duplicates: grey pill, fade out
- +1 score pop floats up from spawn point

**Pause:**
Hover the timer ring → pause button appears. Pausing stops the timer but also locks scoring. Arena blurs behind an overlay: "Paused — no points scored while paused" + Resume button.

**Did you mean:**
Live fuzzy match as player types (Levenshtein, debounced 180ms). Shows below input: "Did you mean [Game Name]?" as a clickable amber link. Enter also accepts it. If already scored, shows "✓ Already got [name]" in green.

**Up-arrow history:** same terminal-style cycling through submitted values.

**Milestone toasts:** drop in from above arena on bronze/silver/gold. Auto-dismiss.

**End screen:**
- Score large (Nunito 900, blue)
- Rank badge
- "Your answers" — amber chips
- "You missed" — grey chips, all possible answers not guessed
- "X out of Y possible answers" subtitle
- Play Again + Share

**Share format:** `⚡ Blitz #014 — Mario Games\n🥇 18/55 in 90s\nidlehours.co.uk/play`

**Answer matching:** normalise input (lowercase, strip punctuation, collapse spaces). Match against a canonical answers list + aliases map. See reference file for the data structure.

**Reference file attached:** `blitz-v2.html`

